<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14098">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/FireSafety.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13213">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      <b>Science of and Hazards of Fire.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13213 mb-requirement-id-13214">
        (a) Explain the concept of fire. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YV8TT9LRBrY" target="_blank"
          >Is Fire a Solid, a Liquid, or a Gas? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/tMDKeBaLWDw" target="_blank"
          >What Is Fire? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13213 mb-requirement-id-13215">
        (b) Name the parts of the fire tetrahedron and the products of
        combustion. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Bd9JWtp-3wI" target="_blank"
          >Understanding the Fire Tetrahedron (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/c7bFL_-vQQA" target="_blank"
          >Fire Tetrahedron | What Are the Elements Required in Order To Ignite
          Fire (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/B0E4PX3e3RE" target="_blank"
          >Science Spotlight: The Combustion of Wood (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_wzJQFl1k9I" target="_blank"
          >Fire and Flame 09—Hydrocarbon Combustion Products (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13213 mb-requirement-id-13216">
        (c) Describe the life cycle of a fire. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/nrMlNAPuJM0" target="_blank"
          >Fire Safety Stages of Fire (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/IEXKxnSPDY0" target="_blank"
          >Stages of a Fire (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/AI5BTfeH05A" target="_blank"
          >The Stages of Fire (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13213 mb-requirement-id-13249">
        (d) Explain the three methods of heat transfer. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8UAI5WFC-2g" target="_blank"
          >Heat Transfer (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13245">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      <b>Fire Extinguishers.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13245 mb-requirement-id-13250">
        (a) Explain the different classes of fires. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/FeLFhRcOWtA" target="_blank"
          >The 5 Different Classes of Fires (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13245 mb-requirement-id-13251">
        (b) Identify the different classes of fire extinguishers and which
        should be used for each class of fire. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/P47BltapQi4" target="_blank"
          >Choose the Right Fire Extinguisher (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13245 mb-requirement-id-13393">
        (c) Demonstrate how to use a fire extinguisher and a fire blanket.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/s1fne087XAk" target="_blank"
          >How To Use a Fire Extinguisher (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/PQV71INDaqY" target="_blank"
          >How To Use a Fire Extinguisher Using the PASS Method (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/DPsceUJPth8" target="_blank"
          >How To Use a Fire Blanket (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13246">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      <b>Fire-related Injuries.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13246 mb-requirement-id-13252">
        (a) Explain and demonstrate the technique of stop, drop, roll, cool, and
        call. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ohntbBVtSKg" target="_blank"
          >Stop, Drop, Roll, Cool, Call (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.nfpa.org/news-blogs-and-articles/blogs/2022/03/31/not-your-mothers-stop-drop-and-roll-evolution-of-a-key-fire-safety-message"
          target="_blank"
          >Stop, Drop, and Roll (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/NzAQR8vHa14" target="_blank"
          >Stop, Drop, Roll, Cover Your Face (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TjHar3TT4tU" target="_blank"
          >Stop, Drop, and Roll (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13246 mb-requirement-id-13253">
        (b) Describe how clothing fires occur, how to prevent them, and how
        clothing can prevent or contribute to burn injuries. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/WFI3M0igb2o" target="_blank"
          >Flame Resistant Fabric Demonstration (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13246 mb-requirement-id-13254">
        (c) Identify the most frequent causes of burn injuries and how to
        prevent them. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/RE8sUY0_RTo" target="_blank"
          >How Common Burns Are, and How They Are Caused (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13246 mb-requirement-id-13255">
        (d) Review the prevention of, symptoms and signs of, and treatment of
        airway burns and carbon monoxide (CO) poisoning.<br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/h7YHWymf7uk" target="_blank"
          >Burn Prevention Tips From Nurses (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.tiktok.com/@redcrosscanada/video/7234607871151967493"
          target="_blank"
          >Signs and Treatment for Carbon Monoxide Poisoning (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13217">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      <b>Origins of Fires.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13217 mb-requirement-id-13218">
        (a) Explain the four classifications of fire origin (natural,
        accidental, incendiary, or undetermined) and give an example of each.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://ocig.com/ocig-institute/undetermined-cause-whats-that-about/"
          target="_blank"
          >Undetermined Cause: What's That About (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13217 mb-requirement-id-13219">
        (b) Describe how a fire classified as incendiary might lead to criminal
        prosecution of a person charged with arson. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/waDjv5UXVMY" target="_blank"
          >Criminal Law: The Crime of Arson (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13247">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      <b>Fire Safety at Home.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13247 mb-requirement-id-13256">
        (a) Describe how to prevent the frequent causes of home fires, including
        unattended cooking, electricity, smoking, clothes dryers, and
        rechargeable batteries. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.injurylawyers.com/blog/5-leading-causes-of-house-fires/"
          target="_blank"
          >5 Most Common Causes of House Fires (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1WOO-Sn2pNI" target="_blank"
          >Fireworks and Wildfires (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13247 mb-requirement-id-13257">
        (b) Describe how to prevent frequent causes of seasonal and
        holiday-related home fires, including fires related to home heating,
        holiday trees, candles, and fireworks. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/6ggmmzFSgpU" target="_blank"
          >How To Prevent Holiday Fires (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13247 mb-requirement-id-13258">
        (c) Demonstrate how to safely light and extinguish a candle. Discuss
        with your counselor, then with your family, how to safely use candles.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.tiktok.com/@naturasoy/video/7060598766985858309"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Properly Extinguish Your Candles (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13247 mb-requirement-id-13259">
        (d) Using the Home Fire Safety Checklist in the
        <em>Fire Safety</em> merit badge pamphlet or one approved by your
        counselor, and with the help of an adult, inspect a home (or a similar
        building near where you live or at a camp) for fire safety hazards.
        Present your completed checklist to your counselor and discuss your
        findings. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Fire%20Safety/Home%20Fire%20Safety%20Checklists.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Home Fire Safety Checklists (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13247 mb-requirement-id-13260">
        (e) Determine if, and what types of, smoke and CO alarms are required in
        homes in your community. List what types of smoke and CO alarms your
        home has, their locations, and their expiration dates. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/LKmhqdq1YnI" target="_blank"
          >Understanding Smoke and Carbon Monoxide Detectors (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13247 mb-requirement-id-13261">
        (f) Demonstrate maintenance of smoke and CO alarms to your counselor and
        review plans to replace expired alarms. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ZMIHE7UeFTU" target="_blank"
          >Home Smoke Alarm Testing and Maintenance (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/JvjLPSja6xU" target="_blank"
          >Smoke Alarm Maintenance (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13247 mb-requirement-id-13262">
        (g) Develop a home fire-escape plan and a fire-drill schedule with your
        family, draw a floor plan of your home with exits marked and a map
        showing your family meeting point, and conduct a home fire drill.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GAiw8PexsOU" target="_blank"
          >How To Survive a Fire (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.usfa.fema.gov/prevention/home-fires/prepare-for-fire/home-fire-escape-plans/"
          target="_blank"
          >Home Fire Escape Plans (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.nfpa.org/downloadable-resources/pdf/how-to-make-a-home-fire-escape-plan"
          target="_blank"
          >Home Fire Escape Plans (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13247 mb-requirement-id-13263">
        (h) Explain what to do and what not to do if you smell natural gas and
        if you smell smoke. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-Z_4TBcXamI" target="_blank"
          >Gas Explosion Prevention (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/RPJGdDOeGx0" target="_blank"
          >What To Do if You Smell Gas (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13247 mb-requirement-id-13264">
        (i) Explain how you would report a fire to have the fire department
        respond. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/JdKG_L5YuB8" target="_blank"
          >How To Call 911 (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/cmEa7Y0ZF5s" target="_blank"
          >What Happens When You Call 911 (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13221">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      <b>Safety with Flammable and Combustible Liquids.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13221 mb-requirement-id-13222">
        (a) Explain what flammable and combustible liquids are commonly used in
        homes and how to safely store them. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ofH8KxvtfZw" target="_blank"
          >Flammable Liquids (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CaDK26g9PxA" target="_blank"
          >Storing Flammable Liquids Safely (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13221 mb-requirement-id-13223">
        (b) Describe the safe way to refuel a liquid-fueled engine, such as a
        lawn mower, outboard motor, farm machine, or automobile with fuel from
        an approved container. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Ujsly7RUr7g" target="_blank"
          >How To Pump Gas (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13221 mb-requirement-id-13224">
        (c) Describe the options available for safely disposing of unwanted
        flammable, combustible, and hazardous substances in your community.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/JJXoaEOC_iI" target="_blank"
          >How To Dispose of Gasoline (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/elXHfp56jMQ" target="_blank"
          >How To Dispose of Old Gasoline (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13230">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      <b>Fire Safety in Public Buildings.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13230 mb-requirement-id-13231">
        (a) Explain how public buildings are designed for fire safety. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.usfa.fema.gov/blog/protecting-people-who-live-or-work-in-high-rises/"
          target="_blank"
          >Fire Safety in High-Rise Buildings (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.nfpa.org/education-and-research/building-and-life-safety/nightclubs-assembly-occupancies"
          target="_blank"
          >Fire Safety in Assembly Occupancies (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13230 mb-requirement-id-13232">
        (b) Explain what fire safety systems and equipment can be found in
        public buildings. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/MFmEYVtaqGY" target="_blank"
          >How To Conduct a Fire Drill (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13230 mb-requirement-id-13233">
        (c) Explain what fire safety precautions you should take when you are in
        a public building. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://ohsonline.com/articles/2016/12/13/nfpa-offers-tips-for-fire-safety-in-public-buildings.aspx"
          target="_blank"
          >NFPA Tips for Fire Safety in Public Buildings (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13248">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      <b>Fire Safety at Camp.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13248 mb-requirement-id-13265">
        (a) Explain how the Leave No Trace Seven Principles and the Outdoor Code
        apply to camping fires. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/knJwXPeiA20" target="_blank"
          >Leave No Trace Principle 5: Minimize Campfire Impacts (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13248 mb-requirement-id-13266">
        (b) Demonstrate lighting a match safely, the proper way to extinguish
        it, and to dispose of it. Explain the similarities and differences
        between safety matches and strike-anywhere matches. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/OinO3OPTWto" target="_blank"
          >How To Light Paper Matches Safely (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/3X_t7bSs_qQ" target="_blank"
          >Fire 101 How To Strike Matches (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13248 mb-requirement-id-13267">
        (c) Explain and demonstrate making sparks with flint and steel or with a
        ferro rod and catching a spark to create a flame. Extinguish the flame
        safely using one of principles of the fire tetrahedron. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/EeR8qutMlWc" target="_blank"
          >Making Fire With Flint and Steel (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/Xl7VPPFQayE" target="_blank"
          >How To Start a Fire With Flint and Steel (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/CXsmV34DqXg" target="_blank"
          >How To Start a Campfire in the Rain? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13248 mb-requirement-id-13268">
        (d) Demonstrate the safe way to start a charcoal fire.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13248 mb-requirement-id-13269">
        (e) Describe three common campsite fire lays. Collect, prepare, and set
        up tinder, kindling, and fuel for a campfire following the Leave No
        Trace Seven Principles and the Outdoor Code. Ignite your fire lay and
        safely extinguish your fire. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/Swgwbk0mcH4" target="_blank"
          >3 Campfire Lays—Through the Eyes of a Thermal Camera (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13248 mb-requirement-id-13270">
        (f) Demonstrate using a camp stove. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.tiktok.com/@therealdadhowdoi/video/7131121409199197482"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Use a Camping Stove (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13248 mb-requirement-id-13271">
        (g) Explain how to set up and keep a campsite safe from fire. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/E0YqVXJ4mkc" target="_blank"
          >Campfire Safety | How To Make a Fire While Camping | How To Put Out a
          Campfire Safely (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13248 mb-requirement-id-13272">
        (h) Develop a lesson plan to teach a fire safety skill or topic, such as
        lighting a candle or a match or a charcoal fire or a lantern or a camp
        stove or using flint and steel or setting up a fire lay. Review your
        lesson plan with your counselor. Teach your skill or topic to one or
        more Scouts using the EDGE method. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://blog.scoutingmagazine.org/2017/05/05/living-on-the-edge-this-is-the-correct-way-to-teach-someone-a-skill"
          target="_blank"
          >The Teaching EDGE: The Best Way To Teach Someone a New Skill
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13234">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      <b>Wildland Fires.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13234 mb-requirement-id-13235">
        (a) List causes of wildland fires and ways to prevent them. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5hghT1W33cY" target="_blank"
          >Wildfires 101 (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13234 mb-requirement-id-13236">
        (b) Explain the social, economic, and environmental consequences of
        wildland fires. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8mQllQnJrhg" target="_blank"
          >How Are Wildfires Making Us Sick (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/RV_OZ430GAs" target="_blank"
          >How Wildfires Affect Water Supply (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/HeOl2N6iLy0" target="_blank"
          >A Better Way To Think Abut Wildland Fires (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13237">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10. </span>
      <b>Careers.</b> Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13237 mb-requirement-id-13238">
        (a) Visit a fire station in-person. Identify the various types of fire
        service vehicles. From the firefighters you meet during your visit,
        learn about the fire prevention activities in your community and about
        their careers. Discuss with your counselor what you learned during your
        tour and interviews. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/aKukWE4CUtU" target="_blank"
          >Fire Station Tour for Kids (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qO6j6oJtK_Q" target="_blank"
          >Memphis Fire Department Virtual Field Trip (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13237 mb-requirement-id-13239">
        (b) Identify three career opportunities that would use skills and
        knowledge in the field of fire safety. Pick one and research the
        training, education, certification requirements, experience, and
        expenses associated with entering the field. Research the prospects for
        employment, starting salary, advancement opportunities and career goals
        associated with this career. Discuss what you learned with your
        counselor and whether you might be interested in this career. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/knS_Dxyu9Rk" target="_blank"
          >How To Become a Firefighter (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/55iglSp3ki0" target="_blank"
          >Wildland Firefighting and Wildland Fire Ecology Jobs (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
